Example raw Purple Air Synoptic dataset

Source: R/data.R
example_pas_raw.Rd

The example_pas_raw dataset provides a quickly loadable version of raw Purple Air synoptic data JSON for practicing and code examples. This dataset contains data for sensors in Washington and Oregon and was generated on 2020-01-03 by running:

  example_pas_raw <- 
    pas_downloadParseData() 
    dplyr::filter(Lon > -125.0 & Lon < -117.0 & Lat > 42.0 & Lat < 49.0)
  save(example_pas_raw, file = "data/example_pas_raw.rda")

This dataset can be converted into a standard pas dataset with:

  pas <- pas_enhanceData(example_pas_raw)

example_pas_raw

Format

A tibble with 961 rows and 33 columns of data.

Source

https://www.purpleair.com/json
